<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 12:39:58 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>低温方舟——沉睡多年</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cryogenic-arks-sleeping-through-the-ages</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 12:39:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cryogenic-arks-sleeping-through-the-ages</guid></item><item><title>学习使脑细胞协同工作，而不是分开工作</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/learning-makes-brain-cells-work-together-not-apart</link><description>当你在某项技能上做得更好时——识别人群中熟悉的面孔，一眼就能发现拼写错误，或者预测游戏中的下一步——你大脑中的感觉神经元会变得更加协调，共享信息而不是更加独立地行动。这是罗切斯特大学及其德尔蒙特神经科学研究所的研究人员在《科学》杂志上发表的一项新研究的结论，该研究挑战了神经科学领域长期以来的假设，即学习通过最大限度地减少神经信号的重复来提高效率。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/learning-makes-brain-cells-work-together-not-apart.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 12:24:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/learning-makes-brain-cells-work-together-not-apart</guid></item><item><title>出院后患者的急性后期护理选择：回顾</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/navigating-postacute-care-options-for-patients-after-hospital-discharge-a-review</link><description>大约 25% 至 40% 的住院成人出院接受治疗&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/navigating-postacute-care-options-for-patients-after-hospital-discharge-a-review2.png" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 12:09:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/navigating-postacute-care-options-for-patients-after-hospital-discharge-a-review</guid></item><item><title>为什么“不朽”的水母可以逆龄衰老——这对人类衰老意味着什么</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/why-the-immortal-jellyfish-can-age-backwards-and-what-that-means-for-human-aging</link><description>海洋中发现的一种微小水母具有逆转其生命周期的非凡能力。这种生物可以从成年体变回水螅体，从本质上重置其生物钟。科学家们正在研究它的 DNA，以了解这个过程。这一发现为衰老和再生提供了新的见解，可能会影响未来的医学研究。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-the-immortal-jellyfish-can-age-backwards-and-what-that-means-for-human-aging.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 11:54:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/why-the-immortal-jellyfish-can-age-backwards-and-what-that-means-for-human-aging</guid></item><item><title>肝窦内皮细胞在肝脏疾病中的作用：健康和病理学的关键参与者</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-role-of-liver-sinusoidal-endothelial-cells-in-liver-diseases-key-players-in-health-and-pathology</link><description>肝窦内皮细胞（LSEC）是一种特殊的内皮细胞，负责协调肝窦内的肝脏稳态。除了在调节肝内血管张力、运输和细胞串扰方面发挥关键作用外，它们的清除和免疫调节作用也使其成为肝病发展的核心。 LSEC 功能障碍包括窗孔丧失、炎症激活以及血管收缩和促血栓功能的获得。强有力的证据表明，保存 LSEC 在病理情况下至关重要，将 LSEC 置于新型治疗和诊断策略的中心。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-role-of-liver-sinusoidal-endothelial-cells-in-liver-diseases-key-players-in-health-and-pathology2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 11:39:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-role-of-liver-sinusoidal-endothelial-cells-in-liver-diseases-key-players-in-health-and-pathology</guid></item><item><title>小鼠晚期阿尔茨海默病的药理学逆转以及人脑中潜在治疗节点的鉴定</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pharmacologic-reversal-of-advanced-alzheimers-disease-in-mice-and-identification-of-potential-therapeutic-nodes-in-human-brain</link><description>在这里，我们展示了 NAD 的药理学恢复&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pharmacologic-reversal-of-advanced-alzheimers-disease-in-mice-and-identification-of-potential-therapeutic-nodes-in-human-brain2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 11:24:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pharmacologic-reversal-of-advanced-alzheimers-disease-in-mice-and-identification-of-potential-therapeutic-nodes-in-human-brain</guid></item><item><title>低剂量多巴酚丁胺输注对急性心肌梗死高危患者 N 端 B 型利钠肽的影响 (DOBERMANN-D)：一项随机临床试验</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/effect-of-low-dose-dobutamine-infusion-on-n-terminal-pro-b-type-natriuretic-peptide-in-at-risk-patients-with-acute-myocardial-infarction-dobermann-d-a-randomized-clinical-trial</link><description>对于有院内 CS 发展风险的 AMI 患者，早期输注多巴酚丁胺不会降低 NT-proBNP 血浆浓度，但会降低 SBP，且不存在安全问题。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/effect-of-low-dose-dobutamine-infusion-on-n-terminal-pro-b-type-natriuretic-peptide-in-at-risk-patients-with-acute-myocardial-infarction-dobermann-d-a-randomized-clinical-trial2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 11:09:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/effect-of-low-dose-dobutamine-infusion-on-n-terminal-pro-b-type-natriuretic-peptide-in-at-risk-patients-with-acute-myocardial-infarction-dobermann-d-a-randomized-clinical-trial</guid></item><item><title>用于测量血压的无袖带装置：美国心脏协会的科学声明</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cuffless-devices-for-the-measurement-of-blood-pressure-a-scientific-statement-from-the-american-heart-association</link><description>无袖血压计有可能增加血压筛查的可及性并克服障碍，特别是对于资源贫乏的社区。来自这些社区的个人——包括来自农村地区、低收入或代表性不足的种族或族裔群体的人——往往比其他人有更高的高血压和不受控制的血压患病率，并且在获得医疗保健服务方面面临障碍，包括定期血压监测和通过 ABPM 确认办公室血压。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cuffless-devices-for-the-measurement-of-blood-pressure-a-scientific-statement-from-the-american-heart-association2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 10:54:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cuffless-devices-for-the-measurement-of-blood-pressure-a-scientific-statement-from-the-american-heart-association</guid></item><item><title>领先时代：克洛诺斯和长寿医学的早期架构</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ahead-of-its-time-kronos-and-the-early-architecture-of-longevity-medicine</link><description>一生中的预防——一生后的保护&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ahead-of-its-time-kronos-and-the-early-architecture-of-longevity-medicine.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 10:39:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ahead-of-its-time-kronos-and-the-early-architecture-of-longevity-medicine</guid></item><item><title>FlyWire 入门，苍蝇的完整连接体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-primer-on-flywire-a-complete-connectome-of-the-fly</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 09 Mar 2026 10:24:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-primer-on-flywire-a-complete-connectome-of-the-fly</guid></item></channel></rss>